Thami Ka-Nkosi An Oslo beach man shot and killed his wife before turning the gun on himself. The shooting occurred on Monday 10 September. According to members of the community, the shooting occurred while the couple were parked in the driveway of a relative’s house. Police spokesperson Captain Petros Mpinge said an investigation is underway. “Cases of murder and inquest are under investigation following the incident that occurred on Monday in Kent Road, Oslo beach, where a man in his mid-thirties shot and fatally wounded a woman in her 30s. According to information we have gathered, the man later shot himself. No one has been arrested. The case is under investigation,” said Mpinge. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  